# Requirements: CalmDo Core

**Defined:** 2026-03-10
**Core Value:** Developer velocity -- new features are faster to build because every file has a clear, predictable home

## v2.0 Requirements

Requirements for CalmDo Core milestone. Each maps to roadmap phases.

### Auth & DX Infrastructure

- [ ] **AUTH-01**: User can sign up and sign in with email + password (in addition to existing OTP and GitHub OAuth)
- [ ] **AUTH-02**: User can reset password via email link
- [ ] **DX-01**: Dev mailbox captures all emails sent during development, viewable at a dev route (like Phoenix's /dev/mailbox)
- [ ] **DX-02**: Lefthook pre-commit hook enforces 100% test coverage on every commit
- [ ] **DX-03**: Playwright E2E tests using feather-testing-core and feather-testing-convex cover all user-facing flows

### Task Core

- [ ] **TASK-01**: User can create a task with title, optional description (markdown), and priority (boolean: high or not)
- [ ] **TASK-02**: User can view their tasks in a "My Tasks" list
- [ ] **TASK-03**: User can edit a task's title, description, and priority
- [ ] **TASK-04**: User can delete a task (with confirmation)
- [ ] **TASK-05**: User can change a task's status through todo → in_progress → done
- [ ] **TASK-06**: User can create a quick task (no project) that is private to them by default
- [ ] **TASK-07**: Quick task auto-flips to shared visibility when assigned to another user
- [ ] **TASK-08**: User can assign a task to any team member
- [ ] **TASK-09**: Unassigned tasks appear in a "Team Pool" view for anyone to grab
- [ ] **TASK-10**: User can drag-reorder tasks within a list (position field)

### Projects

- [ ] **PROJ-01**: User can create a project with name and status (default: active)
- [ ] **PROJ-02**: User can edit a project's name and status
- [ ] **PROJ-03**: User can delete a project (cascades to its tasks and work logs)
- [ ] **PROJ-04**: User can view a projects list filtered by status (active/on_hold/completed/archived)
- [ ] **PROJ-05**: User can assign a task to a project (optional -- tasks can exist without a project)
- [ ] **PROJ-06**: User can view all tasks within a project, filtered by status/assignee/priority
- [ ] **PROJ-07**: Project view shows task count by status

### Subtasks

- [ ] **SUB-01**: User can add subtasks to a task with title and optional assignee
- [ ] **SUB-02**: User can mark a subtask as done
- [ ] **SUB-03**: User can edit a subtask's title and assignee
- [ ] **SUB-04**: User can delete a subtask
- [ ] **SUB-05**: User can reorder subtasks within a task (position field)
- [ ] **SUB-06**: User can promote a subtask to a full task (subtask marked as "promoted" with link to new task)
- [ ] **SUB-07**: Parent task shows subtask completion count (e.g., "3/5 done")

### Work Logs

- [ ] **WLOG-01**: User can add a work log entry to any task (body text + optional time in minutes)
- [ ] **WLOG-02**: User can edit their own work log entries
- [ ] **WLOG-03**: User can delete their own work log entries
- [ ] **WLOG-04**: Task detail shows total time logged across all work log entries

### Activity Logs

- [ ] **ACTV-01**: System auto-logs task events: created, status_changed, assigned, unassigned, edited, deleted
- [ ] **ACTV-02**: System auto-logs project events: created, status_changed, edited
- [ ] **ACTV-03**: System auto-logs subtask events: created, completed, promoted
- [ ] **ACTV-04**: Task detail shows a combined timeline of work logs + activity logs, grouped by date

### Search & Filters

- [ ] **SRCH-01**: User can filter tasks by status (todo/in_progress/done)
- [ ] **SRCH-02**: User can filter tasks by priority (high priority only)
- [ ] **SRCH-03**: User can filter tasks by project
- [ ] **SRCH-04**: User can filter tasks by assignee (me/unassigned/specific person)
- [ ] **SRCH-05**: User can filter projects by status
- [ ] **SRCH-06**: User can text-search across task titles and project names from a search box in the header

### Views

- [ ] **VIEW-01**: My Tasks view -- tasks assigned to current user (quick tasks + project tasks)
- [ ] **VIEW-02**: Team Pool view -- unassigned shared/project tasks available to grab
- [ ] **VIEW-03**: Projects List view -- all projects with status and task counts
- [ ] **VIEW-04**: Project Detail view -- tasks in a project with filters and status summary
- [ ] **VIEW-05**: Task Detail view -- full task with subtasks, work logs, activity timeline
- [ ] **VIEW-06**: Sidebar navigation with My Tasks, Team Pool, Projects section with project list

## Future Requirements

Deferred to later milestones. Tracked but not in current roadmap.

### Organizations (v3.0+)

- **ORG-01**: Multi-org schema with org-scoped queries
- **ORG-02**: Atomic signup (org created with first user)
- **ORG-03**: Org switching UI

### Task Links (v3.0+)

- **LINK-01**: spawned_from relationship between tasks
- **LINK-02**: blocked_by relationship between tasks

### Collaboration (v3.0+)

- **COLLAB-01**: Threaded comments on tasks
- **COLLAB-02**: @mentions in comments
- **COLLAB-03**: Questions as first-class entities
- **COLLAB-04**: Checklist templates (reusable)

### Config System (v3.0+)

- **CFG-01**: Feature manifest files declaring dependencies and settings
- **CFG-02**: calmdo.config.ts with Zod-validated feature selection
- **CFG-03**: Assembler reading config and generating full-stack code
- **CFG-04**: Structured wizard for feature selection

## Out of Scope

| Feature | Reason |
|---------|--------|
| Organization/multi-org layer | Deferred -- user-scoped is sufficient for 2-person team in v2.0 |
| Task Links (spawned_from, blocked_by) | Deferred -- not needed for core task management |
| Comments and mentions | Phase 2 of CalmDo roadmap (collaboration) |
| Kanban board view | Phase 2 of CalmDo roadmap |
| Client visibility | Phase 3 of CalmDo roadmap |
| Permissions/RBAC | Phase 4 of CalmDo roadmap -- all team members have full access in v2.0 |
| Config-driven assembler | v3.0 -- build features first, extract patterns second (research consensus) |
| Runtime feature toggles | Not needed when each client gets separate codebase |
| Real-time notifications | Deep-work friendly -- no push notifications by design |
| Mobile app | Web-only |

